{{Infobox Union |name= Association of Educational Psychologists |country= [[United Kingdom]] |affiliation= [[Trades Union Congress|TUC]], [[General Federation of Trade Unions (UK)|GFTU]] |members= 3,386 (2009)<ref>[http://www.certoffice.org/CertificationOfficer/media/DocumentLibrary/PDFs/706T_2009.PDF Annual Return] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928095112/http://www.certoffice.org/CertificationOfficer/media/DocumentLibrary/PDFs/706T_2009.PDF |date=September 28, 2011 }}, [[Certification Officer]]</ref> |full_name= |native_name= |image= |founded= 1962 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Durham, England|Durham]] |people= Kate Fallon, General Secretary |website= [http://www.aep.org.uk/ aep.org.uk] |footnotes= }}
The '''Association of Educational Psychologists''' is a [[trade union]] in the [[United Kingdom]].
The [[British Psychological Society]] represented [[educational psychologist]]s until 1962, when it received [[Chartered (professional)|chartered]] status. Those members who wished to remain part of a body able to negotiate on their behalf formed the "Association of Educational Psychologists", although it delegated the actual negotiations to the [[National Union of Teachers (UK)|National Union of Teachers]] and the [[Ulster Teachers Union]].<ref name="marsh">Arthur Marsh and Victoria Ryan, ''Historical Directory of Trade Unions'', p.410</ref>
In 1997, the organisation took over negotiation duties from the National Union of Teachers, and in 1999, it affiliated to the [[Trades Union Congress]]. It only began accepting members in Scotland in 2003.<ref name="marsh" />
