{{italic title}} [[File:Foul Play (novel) 1868.jpg|thumb|First edition title page]] '''''Foul Play''''' is an 1869 [[melodramatic]] or [[Sensation novel|sensation]] novel by the British writer [[Charles Reade]]. In [[Victorian Britain]] a clergyman is wrongly convicted of a crime and [[transported]] to Australia. He is shipwrecked with an aristocratic woman on the hitherto uncharted "Godsend Island" in the South Pacific. Eventually he is rescued and vindicated of his crime.
==Adaptations== In 1914 it served as the basis for the American ''[[The Ticket-of-Leave Man (1914 film)|The Ticket-of-Leave Man]]''. In 1920 the novel was adapted into a silent film ''[[Foul Play (1920 film)|Foul Play]]'' directed by [[Edwin J. Collins]] and starring [[Renee Kelly]] and [[Henry Hallett]].
