{{Orphan|date=January 2016}} [[File:7075 Grutas de Cacahuamilpa.jpg|thumb|7075 Grutas de Cacahuamilpa]] '''Cacahuamilpa's Grottos''' (''Grutas de Cacahuamilpa''{{Pronunciation needed}}<!-- as IPA --> in Spanish) is an oil painting finished in 1835 by [[Jean-Baptiste Louis Gros]], after his second visit to the caves in [[Grutas de Cacahuamilpa National Park]], in [[Guerrero]], [[Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Grutas de Cacahuamilpa, 1835-1835|url=http://www.artnet.com/artists/jean-baptiste-louis-baron-gros-gros/grutas-de-cacahuamilpa-bznAZJJaCI9_TzaTCIRFlA2|website=Artnet|accessdate=13 December 2015}}</ref> It is now in the [[Museo Soumaya]], [[Mexico City]].
== Features == The picture, in a naturalist style, shows a group using the rocks as a table. The [[chiaroscuro]] arises from the lights of the expeditioners, giving a Romantic feeling.<ref>{{cite book|title=Museo Soumaya|date=2015|publisher=Fundación Carlos Slim|location=México|isbn=978-607-7805-12-0}}</ref>
